<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,481,690,717]" box="[151,481,690,717]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,481,690,717]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" reason="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,481,690,717]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[151,400,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifrons">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,400,690,717]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Pamphilius latifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1437,762,1077]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
The member of this species group is characterized as follows: upper part of head pilose; facial crest in male rather strongly swollen, bluntly carinate; antennal flagellomere 1 1.7–2.2 × length of flagellomere 2; right mandible bidentate with only basal shoulder to apical tooth; left mandible tridentate, but middle tooth low; wings hyaline; forewing with cell C glabrous; femora entirely pale. Ovipositor sheath appendage small, inconspicuous. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 93" captionStartId="182.[151,250,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-26@182.[151,1435,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="182" captionText="FIGURE 93. Pamphilius latifrons, male, Germany – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) genitalia dorsally, (h) claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876727/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[151,197,906,932]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="9.3" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" unit="g" value="93.0">93g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
): proximal ventral arm of gonostipes normal; apiceps very broad; valviceps rather long, bent outwardly and directed below, without conspicuous dorsoapical process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1437,762,1077]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
Only one Palaearctic species is known (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[635,830,978,1004]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
), which occurs in the Russian Far East. It was formerly regarded as an isolated member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[593,679,1014,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[593,679,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Benes, K." box="[768,904,1014,1040]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="159 - 173" refId="ref72892" refString="Benes, K. (1976) The Siberian species of the genus Pamphilius related to Pamphilius vafer (L.) (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 73, 159 - 173." type="journal article" year="1976">Beneš 1976</bibRefCitation>
) or the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1812" box="[994,1096,1014,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis box="[994,1096,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">P. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Achterberg, C. van &amp; Aartsen, B. van" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref72491" refString="Achterberg, C. van &amp; Aartsen, B. van (1986) The European Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera: Symphyta), with special reference to the Netherlands. Zoologische Verhandelingen, 234, 1 - 98." type="journal article" year="1986">Achterberg &amp; Aartsen 1986</bibRefCitation>
). No molecular data are available. The larvae feed on 
<taxonomicName box="[816,934,1050,1076]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Salicaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[951,1112,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName box="[951,1046,1050,1076]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Populus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1112,1050,1076]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Salix</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
